(Christ Witnesses to Nicodemus on being born
again and what it means. Continued (2):





Jesus
answered,





Verily,
verily, 

I say unto thee,





Except a man be
born 

of water 

and of the Spirit,





he cannot enter

into the kingdom of God.





That which is born of the flesh 

is flesh;





and that which is born of the Spirit 

is spirit.





(John 3:5-6).





***There are several interpretations of the phrase,
"born of water and the Spirit."





***(1): Jesus was referring to water baptism. (Acts
10:43-48)<---To him give all the prophets witness, that through his name
whosoever believeth in him shall receive remission of sins. While Peter yet
spake these words, the Holy Ghost fell on all them which heard the word. And
they of the circumcision which believed were astonished, as many as came with
Peter, because that on the Gentiles also was poured out the gift of the Holy
Ghost. For they heard them speak with tongues, and magnify God. Then answered
Peter, Can any man forbid water, that these should not be baptized, which have
received the Holy Ghost as well as we? And he commanded them to be baptized in
the name of the Lord).





***(2): Water is to be understood as a symbol for the
Holy Spirit. Thus the phrase cold be translated "born of water, even the
Spirit."





***(3): Water is to be understood as a symbol of the
Word of God. (Ephesians 5:26)<---That he might sanctify and cleanse it with
the washing of water by the word). (1 Peter 1:23)<---Being born again, not
of corruptible seed, but of incorruptible, by the word of God, which liveth and
abideth for ever).





***(4): Jesus used the phrase "born of
water" to refer to physical birth. He then used the contrasting phrase
"of the Spirit" to refer to spiritual birth.





***(5): Jesus used the phrase "born of
water" to refer to John the Baptist's baptism.





***(6): Jesus used the Old Testament imagery of
"water" and "wind" to refer to the work of God from above.
(Isaiah 44:3-5)<---For I will pour water upon him that is thirsty, and
floods upon the dry ground: I will pour my (spirit) upon thy seed, and my
(blessing) upon thine offspring: And they shall spring up as among the grass,
as willows by the water courses. One shall say, I am the LORD'S; and another
shall call himself by the name of Jacob; and another shall subscribe with his
hand unto the LORD, and surname himself by the name of Israel.

(Ezekiel 37:9-10)<---Then said he unto me, Prophesy unto the wind, prophesy,
son of man, and say to the wind, Thus saith the Lord GOD; Come from the four
winds, O breath, and breathe upon these slain, that they may live. So I
prophesied as he commanded me, and the (breath) came (into them), and they
lived, and stood up upon their feet, an exceeding great army. (Wind) is an
alternate translation of the term (Spirit) in verse 8.








***(1 Peter 3:21)<---The like
figure whereunto even baptism doth also now save us (not the putting away of
the filth of the flesh, but the answer of a good conscience toward God,) by the
resurrection of Jesus Christ:

snippet.textDisplay:
Yo, fam, guns are so fucking broken when humans manage to get them. Sure, you need to get to level 18 to be able to permanently own a gun, but when you do you're unstoppable. And guns are also versatile, with the variants. Let's go over them.



Pistols:
The easiest gun to get and use. Their small size means they take up very little inventory space, and you're able to get them once you reach level 18. To compensate, they generally deal low damage per bullet. As for notable pistols, or pistols I'd recommend, go with the Glock if you want pure reliability and low size, or the M1911 for a balance between decent damage and good reliability. If you want a pistol that has a high damage stat, go with the Desert Eagle or the Model 500 revolver, both deal the highest damage per shot of any pistol in the game, but they're bulky, negating the small size benefit of other pistols.

Shotguns:
Best used for hunting or in servers where most pvp occurs in close quarters. They have by far the lowest range of any gun type in the game, unless you're running the Slug modification. But they also deal some of the highest damage per shot of any weapon in the game, with lower leveled shotguns even beating out higher leveled rifles. For recommendations, I'd go with any shotgun made by Remington, namely the Model 870. For a pure DPS but still reliable shotgun, I'd go with the M1014, which has the Semi-Auto stat. If you want a shotgun thats between the 870 and the M1014, I'd go with the Model 1897, which has the unique Slam Fire stat, which earned it the nickname of "Trench Gun". In fact, it was so op that the Germans during the World War 1 event were actually demanding the USA to ban the shotgun, but the USA said "lol no u use flamethrowers and gas grenades fuck off" in response.

Rifles:
The best "jack of all traits" gun, and generally the one most used by high-leveled soldier-build humans. It has reliability, long range, and good damage, making it good at all ranges. But it doesn't excel at all ranges, as rifle users generally get bodied by shotgun users, and sniper users absolutely clap rifle users at long range. Notable recommendations are: literally any rifle these things are so fucking good.

Snipers:
The kings of long range. With the highest ranged stat of any equippable weapon in the game, snipers are best used at long range. However, they absolutely SUCK up close, and don't do as well at medium ranges as SMGs or Rifles do. Notable ones include the M24, the AWM, the Barrett M82, and the Mk 14.

SMGs:
A cross between the rifle and the shotgun, they have a fairly mediocre range and damage stat, but make up for it in reliability and rate of fire, having some of the highest ROF of any gun type in the game, with a bunch of SMGs having a rate of fire of over a thousand rounds per minute. Notable recommendations are: Any of the Uzis(Normal, Mini, Micro, and Micro Pro), any of Heckler & Koch's SMGs, and the P90.

Unfortunately, the other types, aka explosives and LMGs, are generally only used in the Military Servers, as those are the only servers where it's legal and accepted by the fanbase to use them.
